        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 19 at 6:46AM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 645 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Markle, or 10 miles northwest of Ossian, moving
northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Yoder, Aboite, Edgerton In Allen County, Roanoke, Spencerville In
Dekalb County, Zulu, Arcola, Saint Joe, Antwerp, Grabill, Rolling
Hills, Nine Mile, Leo-cedarville, St. Joe, Dunfee, Concord, Harlan,
Hessen Cassel, Wallen, and Maples.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 469 between mile markers 0 and 30.
Interstate 69 in Indiana between mile markers 289 and 322.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
